article.headline: Southern Miss. 80
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Jeremy Wise scored 18 points and hit each of his three 3-point attempts to lead Southern Mississippi to a convincing 80-42 win over East Carolina on Wednesday night. Wise also tallied five assists as Southern Miss led from the tipoff, opening up a 47-22 lead at halftime and extending the margin to as many as 43 in the second half. Andre Stephens added 16 points and eight rebounds for the Golden Eagles, and Jarvis Hill contributed 12 points off the bench. The Golden Eagles (16-8, 6-5 Conference USA) shot 56 percent from the field, including 53 percent from 3-point range, while the Pirates shot just 33 percent. Southern Miss also finished with a 45-21 rebounding advantage. East Carolina (5-19, 0-11 C-USA) remains winless in conference play. Courtney Captain led the Pirates with 13 points. Darrell Jenkins added 12.
